      <div class="cap">
        <b>Before:</b> repeated manual checks → ambiguity → re-check loops (time &amp; cost <span class="up">↑</span>).<br>
        <b>After:</b> hash → compare → same/different result → re-verifiable proof (time &amp; cost <span class="down">↓</span>).
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="panel">
    <h3>Why 256?</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Global security standard</li>
      <li>Tiny change → completely different output</li>
      <li>Fixed length: 256-bit (64 hex)</li>
      <li>Deterministic result</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="panel">
    <h3>Misunderstanding Prevention</h3>
    <div class="warn">
      SHA-256 does not prevent tampering.<br>
      It detects change and enables re-verification only.
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer>Accuracy(4)=Truth(2)=Life(4)</footer>
</div>
